-- Bank of Montreal Hires Haycock, Eves Joins PACE, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-11-08T20:16:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-08/bank-of-montreal-hires-haycock-eves-joins-pace-vlaad-says.html
Neil Haycock joined Bank of Montreal
as managing director and head of corporate broking in  London 
from JPMorgan Chase & Co., according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based financial services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * PACE Securities Corp. added former Ontario Premier and
Minister of Finance Ernie Eves as chairman and appointed Gerald
McRae chief compliance officer and director.  * Ronald Cheung joined TriVest Wealth Counsel Ltd. as an
investment analyst in Calgary. Cheung was formerly a research
associate at Jennings Capital Inc.  * Former Toronto-Dominion Bank analyst Doug Young joined
Desjardins Securities Inc.  * Beacon Securities Ltd. added former Casimir Capital Ltd.
institutional equity salesman Keith Gilday in Toronto.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
 edmitrieva1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
